    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-10-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-10-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="132"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d132">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.154/1100</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Collins</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="19" xml:id="d132fn19">The same, October 20, to the American
                        diplomatic missions in Guatemala, Honduras, Nicaragua, and Panamá.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 352</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-10-20">October 20,
                            1936</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In a letter addressed to the Secretary of State
                    on October 14, 1936,<note n="18" xml:id="d132fn18">Not printed.</note> the
                    Acting Secretary of Agriculture stated that Mr. E. W. James of the Bureau of
                    Public Roads of that Department would proceed about October 16 to Panamá, Costa
                    Rica, Nicaragua, Honduras and Guatemala, in connection with work on the
                    Inter-American Highway.</p>
                <p>Please show to Mr. James, should the occasion arise, such courtesies and render
                    to him such assistance as is possible and proper.</p>
                <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sumner Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
